Create an Identity Protection device configuration policy that sets “Disable Windows Hello for Business” to disabled. Target to a group containing users.

Devices > Enroll Devices > Windows Hello for Business > set “Configure Windows Hello for Business” to disabled.

Doing both has worked for me in multiple deployments



Create this .reg file:

Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\PassportForWork]

"Enabled"=dword:00000000

"DisablePostLogonProvisioning"=dword:00000000
